uthlessness made it possible for the emperors' line to continue.   Eminent scholar Guy de la Bédoyère, author of Praetorian, asserts that the women behind the scenes-including Livia, Octavia, and the elder and younger Agrippina-were the true backbone of the dynasty. De la Bédoyère draws on the accounts of ancient Roman historians to revisit a familiar time from a completely fresh vantage point. Anyone who enjoys I, Claudius will be fascinated by this study of dynastic power and gender interplay in ancient Rome.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aWomenzRomexHistory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300240672423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300240672.jpg  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-063899-8  YUP eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017